TextBody:
Hello San,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Tech Support! My name is Ilya and I will be assisting you on this case.

Since you're upgrading from 11.0, I suggest going to 11.6 first and confirming functionality.

Please make snapshots of your StealthAUDIT server and SQL Database Server it uses for data storage.

The upgrade instructions can be found here: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Install/Application/Upgrade/Wizard.htm

Note that once the Enterprise Auditor installation process is complete, it is necessary to go through the Upgrade Wizard. To save your job structure please use Upgrade in Place where possible (outlined in the article).

To download the installation package please navigate to https://www.netwrix.com/my_products.html log in and download version 11.6 (not 12.0).

Let me know if you need further assistance.

Best wishes,
Ilya Kotov
Technical Support Engineer
1-949-407-5125 x7099

Hello San,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Tech Support! My name is Ilya and I will be assisting you on this case.

Since you're upgrading from 11.0, I suggest going to 11.6 first and confirming functionality.

Please make snapshots of your StealthAUDIT server and SQL Database Server it uses for data storage.

The upgrade instructions can be found here: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Install/Application/Upgrade/Wizard.htm

Note that once the Enterprise Auditor installation process is complete, it is necessary to go through the Upgrade Wizard. To save your job structure please use Upgrade in Place where possible (outlined in the article).

To download the installation package please navigate to https://www.netwrix.com/my_products.html log in and download version 11.6 (not 12.0).

Let me know if you need further assistance.

Best wishes,

Subject: AW: AW: AW: AW: AW: Netwrix Support Ticket #442867 -  - AW: Update StealthAudit to the current version    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0OLwmN:ref ]

TextBody:
San,

Thank you for your time today! On this meeting we checked the settings for your AIC. I've noticed that you have followed the article's default port allocation, which would be 481. However, that did not work, and since you've mentioned that you didn't have to specify the port previously in the address bar, and after checking the existing certificates, there was one for 443. After changing to that port in the AIC's config file and restarting the server, everything worked.

I'm going to close this ticket now, and if you'd like to leave some feedback - please complete a survey that will be sent to you afterwards. Any comments are appreciated!

Best wishes,
Ilya Kotov
Technical Support Engineer

Hello San,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Tech Support! My name is Ilya and I will be assisting you on this case.

Since you're upgrading from 11.0, I suggest going to 11.6 first and confirming functionality.

Please make snapshots of your StealthAUDIT server and SQL Database Server it uses for data storage.

The upgrade instructions can be found here: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Install/Application/Upgrade/Wizard.htm

Note that once the Enterprise Auditor installation process is complete, it is necessary to go through the Upgrade Wizard. To save your job structure please use Upgrade in Place where possible (outlined in the article).

To download the installation package please navigate to https://www.netwrix.com/my_products.html log in and download version 11.6 (not 12.0).

Let me know if you need further assistance.
